                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Japanese Minister</gloss> to Acting
                        Secretary of State <persName type="to">Adee</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Japan</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-09-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 51.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Mr. Hioki’s note No. 49, dated
                    September 18, I have the honor to inform you that the intention of my government
                    is to carry out the proposed arrangement for the exchange of the prisoners soon
                    after ratification of the treaty by the respective sovereigns, which becomes
                    immediately operative thereon even before the execution of the usual formalities
                    of exchanging the same.</p>
                <p>I beg to request you to be so good as to further communicate the above to the
                    Russian Government.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">K. Takahira.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
